* A person shall cease to be a member of the Board on any of the following
	* inabilityto perform the functions of his office by reason of infirmity of mind or body;
	* proven misconduct;
	* if he becomes bankrupt or insolvent;
	* if he is convicted of an offence involving fraud or dishonesty;
	* if he fails to attend three consecutive meetings of the Board without reasonable cause;
	* if he resigns by written notice to the Board.
	* (1) The Board shall meet for the dispatch of its business at least 3 times a year and at such times as the Chairman maydetermine.
	* The Chairman shall preside at every meeting of the Board, and in his absence, the members present shall appoint a member from among themselves to preside at that meeting.
	* A minimum of three members of the Board may, by notice in writing signed bythem, request the Chairman to summon a special meeting of the Board for such purposes as may be stated in the notice.
	* The Chairman or, in his absence, the member appointed to act in his behalf shall summon a special meeting within five days of his receipt of the notice referred to in subsection (3).
	* The quorum at any meeting of the Board shall be 6.
	* The Chairman or other person presiding shall have a casting vote where there is an equality of votes.
	* Any proposal circulated among all members and agreed to in writing bya two-thirds majorityof all members shall be of the same force or effect as a decision made at a duly constituted meeting of the Board and shall be incorporated in the minutes of the next succeeding meeting of the Board:
	* Any proposal circulated among all members and agreed to in writing bya two-thirds majorityof all members shall be of the same force or effect as a decision made at a duly constituted meeting of the Board and shall be incorporated in the minutes of the next succeeding meeting of the Board:
 Provided that, if a member requires that such proposal be placed before a meeting of the Board, this subsection shall not apply to such proposal.
	* The Board may co-opt any person to attend and participate in its deliberations on any matter but such person shall not vote on any issue for the decision by the Board.
	* The Board shall cause minutes of all its meetings to be taken and signed by the Chairman and kept in proper form.
	* Subject to this Act, the Board shall regulate its own procedure.
	* (1) A member of the Board who has any interest, whether Disclosure of direct or indirect, in anymatter being considered or to be considered interest. by the Board, shall disclose the nature of his interest to the Board and the disclosure shall be recorded in the minutes of the Board and such member shall not take part in any deliberation or decision of the Board relating to that matter.
	* A member of the Board who contravenes subsection (1) shall be guiltyof misconduct and shall be removed from theBoard.
